<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
Unsigned integer wrap-around can bypass the bounds check. Example: assume sizeof(session->value_2) == 256, off == 200 (the earlier off < sizeof-1 check still holds), and size == SIZE_MAX - 100. Then size + off performs unsigned modular arithmetic and wraps to 99, which is < 256, so the condition (size + off >= sizeof(session->value_2)) is false. The code will not crop size and the subsequent memcpy(&session->value_2[off], data, size) will attempt to copy a very large number of bytes and overflow the buffer. Therefore the fragment can lead to out-of-bounds access and violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.17.
</scenario>

